cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with unsupervised classification of hyperspectral images using a graph-based nonlocal total variation method. This involves image processing, machine learning, and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and graphics (cs.GR). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
